        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 4:36PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 436 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of McLain, or 12 miles northeast of Wiggins, moving
west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Perry and
northeastern Stone Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
